2500|$|The IRS, state, {{and local}} tax {{authorities}} may examine a tax return and propose changes. [...] Changes to tax returns {{may be made}} with minimal advance involvement by taxpayers, such as changes to wage or dividend income to correct errors. [...] Other examination of returns may require extensive taxpayer involvement, such as an audit by the IRS. [...] These audits often require <b>that</b> <b>taxpayers</b> provide the IRS or other tax authority access to records of income and deductions. [...] Audits of businesses are usually conducted by IRS personnel at the business location.|$|E
